OL,3,CTerrestrial TV saved from 2030 cliff
OL,4,Cedge
OL,6,FSuch was the concern that terrestrial
OL,7,FTV frequency allocations would be
OL,8,Frescinded after 2030 that Ofcom was
OL,9,Finstructed to insert a revocation
OL,10,Fclause on all new multiplex licences.
OL,12,FWhether Ofcom exercises that right
OL,13,Fwill not be down to the WRC, but
OL,14,Fdecisions made in the UK about the
OL,15,Ffuture of terrestrial TV. It's due to
OL,16,Freport back to Government in 2025
OL,17,Ffollowing a consultation.
OL,19,FContinental broadcasters were busy
OL,20,Flobbying to 'save our spectrum' in the
OL,21,Fpast year. In the UK, tumbleweeds.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/22
