OL,6,FFrequency allocations are based on
OL,7,Fthree global regions. The UK, Europe,
OL,8,FMiddle East and Africa are part of the
OL,9,Faforementioned ITU Region 1.
OL,11,FWithin this region, some countries in
OL,12,Fthe Middle East, including the UAE,
OL,13,Fhave been allowed to reallocate 614 `
OL,14,F694 MHz for primary use by mobile
OL,15,Fcompanies.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G17/22
