OL,4,Cedge
OL,6,FAcross ITU Region 2 (the Americas),
OL,7,Fbroadcasting continues to have
OL,8,Fallocations in the UHF band (primary
OL,9,Fallocation in 470 ` 512 MHz and 614 `
OL,10,F698 MHz, alongside secondary
OL,11,Fallocations for fixed and mobile
OL,12,Fservices; exclusive use of 512 ` 608
OL,13,FMHz, co-primary use with mobile on 698
OL,14,F` 806 MHz).
OL,16,FActual use differs considerably from
OL,17,Fcountry to country and realistically,
OL,18,Fmobile use dominates. The USA, for
OL,19,Fexample has mobile services in the 600
OL,20,FMHz band, with terrestrial broadcasts
OL,21,Fon lower frequencies.
