OL,6,FIn Region 3 (Asia, excluding Middle
OL,7,FEast plus Oceania), broadcasting has
OL,8,Fco-primary allocations, meaning it has
OL,9,Fno exclusive rights over spectrum.
OL,11,FHere's an overview from the WRC-23
OL,12,FProvisional Final Acts document, which
OL,13,Fdoesn't include the various country-
OL,14,Fspecific additions, modifications, and
OL,15,Fadditional allocations, such as the
OL,16,Fsecondary allocation for PMSE and
OL,17,Fmobile in the UK and Ireland.
OL,19,FNot at all. I've heard that the 600
OL,20,FMHz chunk of spectrum will be
OL,21,Fdiscussed at WRC-31 in a decision that
OL,22,Fwould affect frequency use by 2040.
